        "content": "<p>Is this in Mathlib?</p>\n<p><code> G.Colorable 2 ↔ ∀ u, ∀ (w : G.Walk u u), ¬ Odd w.length</code></p>\n<p>I can see  <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Combinatorics/SimpleGraph/ConcreteColorings.html#SimpleGraph.Walk.three_le_chromaticNumber_of_odd_loop\"><code>Walk.three_le_chromaticNumber_of_odd_loop</code></a> but the other direction would seem to require something like </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">G</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Colorable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↔</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∀</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">G</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">ConnectedComponent</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">G</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">induce</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Colorable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>which I also can't see. </p>\n<p>Am I missing something obvious? (If not I'd be happy to add these.)</p>",
